HEADWORD: Opisthobranchiata
<hw>O*pis`tho*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>'o`pisqen</grk> behind + <?/ gills.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of gastropod Mollusca, in which the
breathing organs are usually situated behind the heart. It includes the
tectibranchs and nudibranchs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

